61 Then Virgil said: "Quickly tell him:
62 'I am not he, I am not he whom you think'";
63 and I answered as I was bidden.

64 Whereupon the spirit twisted all his feet;
65 then, sighing and in a voice of weeping,
66 he said to me: "Then what do you ask of me?

67 If you care so much to know who I am,
68 that you have therefore run along the bank,
69 know that I was clothed in the great mantle;

97 Therefore stay where you are, for you are rightly punished;
98 and look well at the ill-gotten money
99 which made you bold against Charles.

103 I would use even graver words;
104 for your avarice saddens the world,
105 treading down the good and lifting up the wicked.

106 Of you shepherds the Evangelist was aware,
107 when she who sits upon the waters
108 was seen by him to play the harlot with kings;

112 You have made a god of gold and silver;
113 and what else is the difference between you and the idolaters,
114 except that they worship one, and you a hundred?

124 Therefore he took me in both his arms;
125 and after he had me all to his breast,
126 he remounted by the way he had descended.
